        chain and service network spanning five foodservice categories. For a hotel kitchen with a Jackson RackStar
        conveyor in the dish room, two Hoshizaki KM ice machines behind the bar, and a Hoshizaki reach-in on the
        line, the Alliance means one service call resolves three pieces of equipment. No LA competitor writes this
        narrative because no LA competitor services all five Alliance brands from the same parts account.
      </p>
      <p>
        Jackson is also the rare commercial dishwasher brand with a credible California parts story. Hobart ships
        most parts from the Troy, Ohio plant — 5 to 10 business days to LA. Champion and CMA ship from Winston-Salem,
        North Carolina — similar timeline. Jackson ships common parts out of the Hoshizaki Peachtree City, Georgia
        warehouse via the California regional, and that's usually a 1-to-3-day turnaround for LA. When a RackStar
        conveyor goes down on a Friday, the ship date is the story.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

